description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Plug, 14-19, Skt Zinc Nickel
info:
Gray Zinc Nickel (ZnNi) Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial Gray Zinc Nickel (ZnNi) Circular Connectors feature cadmium-free, RoHS-compliant plating that is suitable for harsh environments. These ZnNi-plated connectors are originally developed for harsh marine environments and feature a -65°C to +200°C temperature range and withstand 500 hours of salt spray. These connectors offer <2.5mΩ conductivity and consist of gray zinc over an electroless nickel base, giving the connector a light gunmetal gray appearance. This plating delivers high corrosion resistance and has no significant galvanic reaction when mated with leading standard-market plating options.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 20P Shell Size 28 Straight Plug
info:
5015 Series Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial 5015 Series Connectors are rugged and versatile. These environmentally resistant connectors offer proven electrical capability for a cost-effective solution. The medium to heavyweight cylindrical 5015 connectors are available in a range of shell styles, shell sizes, and service classes. They are designed to MIL-DTL-5015 (SAE-AS50151) standards. Amphenol Industrial 5015 Connectors offer more than 300 insert patterns and are available with solder or crimp contacts as well as RADSOK® contacts in certain sub-series.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Jam Nut Recpt Nickel plate
info:
Amphe-Lite M3 Circular MIL-Spec Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial Amphe-Lite M3 Circular MIL-Spec Connectors are designed to obtain metal-to-metal coupling for superior EMI shielding capability. Amphe-Lite Metal is 100% scoop-proof and features high-density contact arrangements. This Amphenol Industrial connector series provides self-locking, quick disconnect threaded coupling as well as locksmith keying. The five key-way polarization of these connectors provides five alternate rotations. This circular connector series also features corrosion resistance. Shells of Gray ZnNi playing can withstand a 500-hour salt spray exposure. Moisture resistance through an improved interfacial seal design prevents electrolytic erosion of contacts.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 6P PLG SZ 17 SKT CBL MNT
info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Backshells BACKSHELL NON ENV EMI/RFI ST NIC SZ 23
info:
Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps help to tidy up the cable after termination and provide strain relief at the termination area. The clamps are offered in environmental and non-environmental options, as well as EMI/RFI. The components are available in black zinc nickel, adding to the existing finishes in olive drab gray cadmium, tin, or nickel with a variety of shell sizes 11 through 48. Amphenol Pcd Backshell Clamps meet MIL-DTL-38999, MIL-DTL-26482 Series II, MIL-DTL-83723 Series I and II, MIL-DTL-24308, and MIL-DTL-83513.

info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series II Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace MIL-DTL-38999 Series II consists of subminiature circular connectors designed to offer high reliability and high contact density with maximum weight and space savings. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series II Circular Connectors feature a lightweight, space-saving design, 3-point bayonet lock system, and error-proof alternate positioning. Amphenol Aerospace MIL-DTL-38999 Series II Circular Connectors are ideally suited for industrial applications, military and commercial air, military vehicles, missiles and ordnance, and C4ISR.

info:

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector MS/TRI-START HERMETIC
info:
Hermetic Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Hermetic Circular Connectors maintain system integrity in applications where reliability and performance are critical, such as gas-tight barriers or areas with high-pressure differentials. A wide range of materials and manufacturing capabilities are used to provide consumer and MIL-Spec products for glass-to-metal seals and lightweight epoxy backfilled solutions. The epoxy-sealed connectors are a lightweight alternative to glass-sealed hermetic connectors for use in avionics and other weight-sensitive applications where a high level of sealing is required. Epoxy-sealed connectors are an optimal solution when increasingly stringent sealing requirements must be met.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Straight Plug Series I
info:
LJT MIL-DTL-38999 Series I Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace LJT Connectors are subminiature cylindrical connectors qualified to MIL-DTL-38999 Series I. Amphenol Aerospace LJT Connectors provide scoop-proof contact protection and grounding fingers for electromagnetic interference (EMI) shielding. A five key / keyway design eliminates mismating and ensures error-proof alternate positioning. The series is designed for use in commercial and military aerospace applications.
